Crap movie!!! First time I cried for buying ticket. I'm  big fan of star wars  but this one makes me hate all the series
I didn't think Disney could do worse than the last jedi

This movie feels designed by committee, but the committee is a classroom of young teenagers who like lightsabers and force lightning. Seemingly no creative vision, no driving thread, only loosely sewn together ideas that disappointingly culminate in a "this is the most Star Wars, right?" kinda way.

Someone must've thought that there wasn't enough nostalgia in the sequel trilogy so they just dumped everything "Star Wars" they could think of into this movie. The plot is just convoluted, a big hunt for a MacGuffin to find the big bad that apparently concentrates everything evil there is, fitting content to fill 3 movies into one. The story beats from previous movies is barely recognized at all, it's more like the creators just realized it's only one film left and they had plans for a whole trilogy.
On the plus side, the movie is visually stunning, and music as well as sound design are sublime. 

Nothing about its execution appears bold or innovative, on the contrary the most interesting results from the previous movie are ridiculed or retconned. And the moments where it emotionally connected are cheapened by too convenient resolutions. Instead of a strong conclusion to the saga we get a nostalgia-driven firework of fanservice. It's a lot, but it isn't much.

Despite some pacing issues and the occasional bits of clunky dialogue, this movie is an amazing ride. It's packed to the brim and a worthy conclusion to the sequel trilogy - although I wouldn't say it felt like the end of the entire saga. A must-see for Star Wars fans who will appreciate its well done fan-service moments.

I feel that the Star Was saga starting with the Force Awakens until  the Rise of Skywalker have all gone to crap since Disney took over. The original Star Wars from the 70's-80's are way better because Fox Studios/Lucasfilms did that saga. Nothing beats the original and the actors were way better back then.

This movie is fantastic.  There are so many awesome moments, watching it 2 or 3 times is almost a must.  I have no idea what critics are complaining about but if you love Star Wars and want to see a great end to this saga...go see this and ignore what the naysayers think and say.
action packed from start to finish a great ending to a a even greater franchise!
